Denote by (\alpha) the functional equation $f\left(x\right)+f\left(1-\frac{1}{x}\right)=\log |x|.$</think> <answer> Let $x=2007$. Then
\begin{align*}
f(2007)+f\left(1-\frac{1}{2007}\right) &= \log\lvert 2007\rvert \\
&= \log 2007. 
\end{align*}
So $f(2007)=\log 2007 - f\left(\frac{2006}{2007}\right)$. From the functional equation, we get 
\begin{align*}
f\left(\frac{2006}{2007}\right) + f\left(1 - \frac{2007}{2006}\right) &= \log\left\lvert\frac{2006}{2007}\right\rvert \\
&= \log \frac{2006}{2007}. 
\end{align*}
But $1-\dfrac{2007}{2006}=\dfrac{1}{2006}$. Thus, we get \[f\left(\frac{2006}{2007}\right) + f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right) = \log\frac{2006}{2007}. \]
Similarly, putting $x=\dfrac{1}{2006}$, we find \[f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right) + f\left(1-2006\right) = \log\left\lvert\frac{1}{2006}\right\rvert.\] Or 
\[f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right) + f(-2005) = \log\frac{1}{2006}. \]So $f\left(-2005\right)=\log\frac{1}{2006}-f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right)$. Therefore, we have \[f(2007)-f(2005) = \log 2007 - \left(\log 2006 - f\left(-2005\right)\right).\]Then \begin{align*}
f(2007)-f(2005) &= \log 2007 - \log 2006 + f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right)-f\left(\frac{2006}{2007}\right) \\
&= \log\frac{2007}{2006} - \left(\log\frac{2006}{2007}-\log 2007\right) 
\end{align*}By putting $x=\dfrac{1}{2006}$ in ($\alpha$), we can conclude that \[f\left(\frac{1}{2006}\right) = \log \frac{2006}{2007} - \log 2007. \]Hence, \begin{align*}
f(2007)-f(2005) &= \log\frac{2007}{2006} - \left(\log\frac{2006}{2007}-\log 2007\right) \\
&= \log \frac{2007}{2006}+\log 2007-\log 2006 \\
&= \boxed{\log 2007^2}. 
\end{align*></answer>

